Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read what you can and cannot do

This page gives you guidance on how to stay safely in Burundi as a visitor, if you are unable to return to the UK.
Moving around in country
Everyone should comply with the measures put in place in Burundi to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
If you cannot leave Burundi at this time, you should:
follow the advice of local authorities, including local measures to help minimise your risk of exposure to coronavirus
find accommodation thatâ€™s suitable for your needs
keep in regular contact with family and friends at home, so they know you are safe and well
See more information and advice about staying where you are if you cannot return to the UK.
Visas
The Burundi authorities currently will no longer issue new visas, and will only renew visas for those already in Burundi.
Further information
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
